                         "Memories of Love," a jewel-cabinet piece by Damien Hirst. Containing 6,000 laboratory-produced gemstones, it was priced at 2.35 million pounds. The work was offered by the London-based dealers White Cube at the Art Basel fair in Switzerland and sold to a European collector. 
                       
                     
                                        
           
                     "Memories of Love," a jewel-cabinet piece by Damien Hirst. Containing 6,000 laboratory-produced gemstones, it was priced at 2.35 million pounds. The work was offered by the London-based dealers White Cube at the Art Basel fair in Switzerland and sold to a European collector.  Photographer: Gareth Brown/White Cube via Bloomberg  
                   
    

                 
           
                            
                     
